\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 ****The book\'92s epilogue indeed proposes that the fall or political vacuum of Pedro Castillo (following his attempt to close Congress) opened the 
\f0\b Sixth Critical Juncture
\f1\b0 \'97termed the "critical juncture of neoliberalism"\'97because this event acted as a catalyst that brought to the surface and condensed multiple accumulated crises and unresolved historical contradictions.\
According to the authors, this critical juncture is the condensation of three colliding "moments" or temporal dimensions:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Current Moment (Immediate Rupture and Social Polarization):
\f1\b0  This outbreak is characterized by an open confrontation between the extreme right and factual powers on one side, and a "democratizing popular movement" made up of peasants, indigenous groups, and women (mainly from the southern regions) on the other. Castillo's ouster and the subsequent protests laid bare the profound contempt of the elites for the popular will and the political agency of citizens from the provinces. This resulted in severe police and military repression by the State, which treated the protesters as enemies rather than citizens, leaving a toll of 47 dead and over 1,200 injured.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Medium-Term Moment (The Failure of 30 Years of Neoliberalism):
\f1\b0  The crisis sparked by Castillo's departure condensed the discontent accumulated over three decades of the neoliberal model's hegemony. It exposed suffocating structural contradictions, such as the urgent need to change the primary-export economic model, the profoundly unequal reach of the state in providing public goods across the national territory, and the collapse of the political, electoral, and representational systems.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Long-Term Historical Moment (Unresolved Historical Legacies):
\f1\b0  Finally, the current crisis brought to the forefront underlying problems that Peru has dragged along since its colonial and republican eras. These include the urgency of a delayed democratic revolution to eliminate discrimination and privileges; the recognition of the country as a pluricultural nation-state in the face of a persistent racist and classist matrix used by elites to stigmatize "the other"; and the struggle to rescue the "common good," which ended up being devoured by neoliberal privatization and turned into private business.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 In conclusion, Pedro Castillo's fall is not presented as a mere governmental crisis, but as the rupture event that detonated all the accumulated discontent against the economic model of the last 30 years. It laid bare territorial inequalities, structural racism, and the total disconnection of the State from Peruvian society.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
